# Diagnosis input CSV. One *group* per data line.
#
# Format:
#   - Each data line is one logical diagnosis step:
#       <SW cmd 1>|<SW cmd 2>|...|<SW cmd N>
#     The host sends every SW command in order (CR appended automatically),
#     reads one reply line per SW (typically "OK"/"FAIL").
#   - After all SW in the group, the host runs three *fixed* wavelength/source
#     sequences (not from this file), each followed by pd/opm:
#         (1) SFP_1550:  WL 1550, SW 3 1 1,  pd 1, opm 3 1
#         (2) SFP_1310:  WL 1310, SW 3 1 4,  pd 1, opm 3 1
#         (3) Laser_1310: WL 1310, SW 3 1 8, pd 1, opm 3 1
#     One reply line is read after each command.
#   - Tokens are separated by '|'. Whitespace around tokens is trimmed.
#   - Lines starting with '#' or ';' are comments. The trimmed text after
#     the marker is attached as the *label* of the next data line (used for
#     reporting only; not sent over serial).
#   - UTF-8 BOM on the first line is tolerated.
#
# Result CSV: output\diagnosis_<yyyymmdd_HHMMSS>.csv
#   step,label,sw_count,sw_ok_count,sw_cmds,sw_replies,
#   s1_* .. s3_* (wl1550, sw3, wl1310, pd, opm; unused WL column empty per scenario), total_ms

# CH343
SW 1 1 20|SW 1 2 52|SW 2 20 1|SW 2 52 1

